attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the GoPro, inspects it but does not know how to open the battery door. The instructor tells the student to pull the battery door up from the other side. The student tries to open the battery door again but fails.  The student holds the GoPro with the other hand and tries to open the battery door again but fails. The student inspects the battery door and the instructor tells the student to lift it up, outside of the GoPro. The student opens the battery door, inspects the battery but does not know how to remove it. The instructor tells the student to pull the battery from the strap. The student removes the battery and places it on the table. The student grabs the new battery, inserts it on the slot and closes the battery door. The student inspects the GoPro looking for the Sd card slot and the instructor tells the student it is located in the battery slot. The student opens the battery door, pushes the Sd card and removes it. The student places the old Sd card on the table and grabs the new Sd card. The student incorrectly inserts the new Sd card in the slot, takes it out and inserts it incorrectly again. The student tries to adjust the Sd card in the slot but fails. The student takes out the Sd card, flips it and inserts it again. The student pushes the Sd card and closes the battery door. The student inspects the GoPro looking for its on/off button, finds it and presses it. The student presses and holds the on/off button of the GoPro but releases it too soon. The student presses and holds the on/off button of the GoPro again and turns it off. The student presses the on/off button and turns it on. The student presses and holds the on/off button of the GoPro and turns it off. The student grabs the strap and inspects the GoPro. The student inspects the strap but does not know how to put the GoPro on it. The student opens the mount of the GoPro but does not know how to put the GoPro on the strap. The instructor tells the student to remove the lock screw first. The student removes the lock screw of the strap and places it on the table. The student tries to assemble the GoPro on the strap but fails. The student assembles the GoPro on the strap, grabs the lock screw and screws the GoPro and strap together.  The student removes the lock screw, places it on the table and disassembles the GoPro from the strap. The student places the GoPro on the table, grabs the lock screw and inserts it on the strap. The student places the strap on the table, grabs the tripod and handheld grip but does not know what to do next. The instructor tells the student to grab the handheld grip. The student grabs the handheld grip, lifts the GoPro and places it back on the table. The student removes the lock screw from the handheld grip, places it on the table and grabs the GoPro. The student tries to assemble the GoPro on the handheld grip but fails.  The student assembles the GoPro on the handheld grip, grabs the lock screw and incorrectly inserts it on the handheld grip. The student screws the lock screw but fails. The student removes the lock screw, adjusts the GoPro on the handheld grip and inserts the lock screw again.  The student screws the GoPro and handheld grip together. The student removes the lock screw, disassembles the GoPro from the handheld grip, places the GoPro on the table and screws back the lock screw in the handheld grip. The student places the handheld grip on the table, moves the GoPro on the table and grabs the tripod. The student adjusts the top part of the tripod and removes its lock screw. The student places the lock screw on the table, grabs the GoPro and assembles the GoPro on the tripod. The student grabs the lock screw, inserts it and screws the GoPro and tripod together. The student spreads the legs of the tripod and closes them back again. The student removes the lock screw and places it on the table. The student disassembles the GoPro from the tripod, closes its mount and places the GoPro on the table. The student grabs the lock screw, screws it into the tripod and places the tripod on the table. The student moves the strap closer to the handheld grip, tripod and GoPro on the table.
